1
00:00:03,745 --> 00:00:07,545
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A MAIDEN IN LOVE.

2
00:00:07,545 --> 00:00:10,778
"I WANT TO TELL MY BELOVED
HOW I FEEL,

3
00:00:10,778 --> 00:00:14,945
BUT MY LOVE MIGHT BE OVER
THE MOMENT I CONFESS IT."

4
00:00:14,945 --> 00:00:18,812
EVERY DAY, SHE SUFFERED,
AGONIZING IN THIS WAY.

5
00:00:18,812 --> 00:00:22,645
SHE TOOK NO MEALS,
AND EVEN SLEEP EVADED HER.

6
00:00:22,645 --> 00:00:24,445
EVENTUALLY, SHE DIED

7
00:00:24,445 --> 00:00:29,212
WITHOUT EVER HAVING BEEN ABLE
TO COMMUNICATE HER FEELINGS,

8
00:00:29,212 --> 00:00:32,345
BUT THE MAN SHE LOVED
MARRIED ANOTHER WOMAN

9
00:00:32,345 --> 00:00:34,312
AND LIVED HAPPILY EVER AFTER

10
00:00:34,312 --> 00:00:36,478
WITHOUT EVEN
THE SLIGHTEST INKLING

11
00:00:36,478 --> 00:00:40,645
THAT SHE HAD EVER EXISTED.

12
00:00:40,645 --> 00:00:43,112
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

13
00:00:55,345 --> 00:00:58,478
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

14
00:01:23,412 --> 00:01:25,812
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

15
00:02:08,778 --> 00:02:11,845
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"FINAL WALTZ AND APOTHEOSIS"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

16
00:02:33,056 --> 00:02:35,089
-QUACK?

17
00:02:35,089 --> 00:02:36,423
OH!

18
00:02:36,423 --> 00:02:40,823
I FELL ASLEEP WHILE I WAS
STILL A DUCK, IN FAKIR'S ARMS.

19
00:02:40,823 --> 00:02:41,889
OH.

20
00:02:41,889 --> 00:02:45,323
I WONDER IF FAKIR
BANDAGED THIS FOR ME.

21
00:02:46,989 --> 00:02:48,556
QUACK!

22
00:02:48,556 --> 00:02:49,856
HUH?

23
00:02:49,856 --> 00:02:51,389
QUACK?

24
00:02:52,423 --> 00:02:54,823
QUACK?
THEY'RE STOPPED?

25
00:02:54,823 --> 00:02:57,423
-CONGRATULATIONS, LITTLE DUCK.

26
00:02:57,423 --> 00:02:58,923
-QUACK.

27
00:02:58,923 --> 00:03:02,323
-THE SENSE OF PRIDE
HAS RETURNED TO THE PRINCE.

28
00:03:02,323 --> 00:03:04,323
-[ GASPS ]

29
00:03:04,323 --> 00:03:05,989
QUAAAACK!

30
00:03:05,989 --> 00:03:07,323
QUACK!

31
00:03:07,323 --> 00:03:10,356
-ALL THE WANDERING SHARDS
OF THE PRINCE'S HEART

32
00:03:10,356 --> 00:03:11,589
HAVE RETURNED NOW.

33
00:03:11,589 --> 00:03:12,956
-WHAT? REALLY?

34
00:03:12,956 --> 00:03:15,256
SO, RIGHT NOW, HE'S...

35
00:03:15,256 --> 00:03:17,156
-YES, HE MUST BE ENJOYING

36
00:03:17,156 --> 00:03:20,223
SOME EXCRUCIATING MISERY
RIGHT ABOUT NOW

37
00:03:20,223 --> 00:03:22,589
-WHAT?
-BECAUSE THE DEAR, BRAVE PRINCE

38
00:03:22,589 --> 00:03:25,623
DOESN'T QUITE HAVE ALL
OF THE HEART SHARDS BACK YET.

39
00:03:25,623 --> 00:03:28,389
-WHAT?! BUT YOU JUST SAID
THEY'D ALL RETURNED!

40
00:03:28,389 --> 00:03:29,723
MR. DROSSELMEYER?

41
00:03:29,723 --> 00:03:31,589
-ALL THE WANDERING SHARDS

42
00:03:31,589 --> 00:03:34,956
HIDDEN INSIDE
CHINKS IN OTHER PEOPLE'S HEARTS,

43
00:03:34,956 --> 00:03:38,389
BUT UNFORTUNATELY,
THOSE AREN'T ALL THE SHARDS.

44
00:03:38,389 --> 00:03:40,056
-OH. REALLY?
-OF COURSE.

45
00:03:40,056 --> 00:03:43,256
HIS HEART HAS TO KEEP THE RAVEN
FROM MOVING, AFTER ALL.

46
00:03:43,256 --> 00:03:44,923
THAT IS WHY IT WAS SHATTERED.

47
00:03:44,923 --> 00:03:45,756
-THEN...

48
00:03:45,756 --> 00:03:47,289
-OH, I HAVE NO TIME FOR THIS.

49
00:03:47,289 --> 00:03:49,789
-WAIT! COME BACK!
WHAT SHOULD I DO, THEN?

50
00:03:49,789 --> 00:03:51,356
WHERE'S THE REST OF HIS HEART?

51
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:54,023
THE PRINCE'S HEART
IS BEING DYED IN RAVEN'S BLOOD!

52
00:03:54,023 --> 00:03:56,356
CAN I PUT IT BACK TO NORMAL?
CAN'T YOU TELL ME?

53
00:03:56,356 --> 00:03:58,056
-BYE-BYE, LITTLE DUCK.

54
00:03:58,056 --> 00:04:01,323
WE'LL HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY
TO MEET AGAIN...

55
00:04:01,323 --> 00:04:02,889
WHEN I FEEL LIKE IT.

56
00:04:02,889 --> 00:04:04,723
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

57
00:04:04,723 --> 00:04:07,156
[ WATER SPLASHES ]
-AAH!

58
00:04:07,156 --> 00:04:07,989
-HUH?

59
00:04:07,989 --> 00:04:10,389
-OH! DID SHE DISAPPEAR, ZURA?

60
00:04:10,389 --> 00:04:11,223
-OH!

61
00:04:11,223 --> 00:04:12,723
[ DOG BARKS ]

62
00:04:12,723 --> 00:04:15,189
-WHAT'S THAT?
YOU SAY YOU MET DROSSELMEYER?

63
00:04:15,189 --> 00:04:16,389
-YEAH.

64
00:04:16,389 --> 00:04:19,389
IT LOOKS LIKE
WHENEVER I MEET DROSSELMEYER,

65
00:04:19,389 --> 00:04:20,756
TIME SOMEHOW STOPS.

66
00:04:20,756 --> 00:04:23,189
YOU CAN COME IN NOW.

67
00:04:23,189 --> 00:04:24,623
-AND THEN?

68
00:04:24,623 --> 00:04:26,689
-HE SAID
THE REST OF THE HEART SHARDS

69
00:04:26,689 --> 00:04:28,123
WERE SEALING AWAY THE RAVEN

70
00:04:28,123 --> 00:04:31,456
AND ALSO THAT THE HEART SHARDS
I RETURNED TO MYTHO

71
00:04:31,456 --> 00:04:33,456
ARE CAUSING HIM A LOT OF PAIN.

72
00:04:33,456 --> 00:04:35,256
-SO, WHAT OF IT?

73
00:04:35,256 --> 00:04:36,556
-[ GASPS ]

74
00:04:36,556 --> 00:04:38,656
-IF DROSSELMEYER IS RIGHT,
THAT MOMENT

75
00:04:38,656 --> 00:04:40,756
WHEN ALL THE HEART SHARDS
ARE RETURNED

76
00:04:40,756 --> 00:04:42,756
WILL SEE
THE RAVEN'S RESURRECTION --

77
00:04:42,756 --> 00:04:44,956
IN OTHER WORDS,
THE START OF THE BATTLE.

78
00:04:44,956 --> 00:04:46,289
-[ GASPS ]

79
00:04:46,289 --> 00:04:48,589
-MYTHO MUST BE PREPARED
FOR SOME SUFFERING ALREADY.

80
00:04:48,589 --> 00:04:51,289
IF YOU AREN'T PREPARED
TO HANDLE THAT, AS WELL,

81
00:04:51,289 --> 00:04:53,456
YOU SHOULD STOP BEING
PRINCESS TUTU.

82
00:04:53,456 --> 00:04:55,189
I'LL PROTECT MYTHO
WITH MY SWORD.

83
00:04:55,189 --> 00:04:57,156
-I WISH YOU WEREN'T
ALWAYS GOING AROUND

84
00:04:57,156 --> 00:04:58,423
SWINGING SWORDS AND STUFF.

85
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,423
I MEAN,
IT'S REALLY DANGEROUS, YOU KNOW?

86
00:05:00,423 --> 00:05:02,656
-SO, YOU'RE SAYING
I'M INCAPABLE AS A KNIGHT.

87
00:05:02,656 --> 00:05:04,623
IS THAT WHAT YOU THINK?
-THAT'S NOT IT!

88
00:05:04,623 --> 00:05:07,456
YOU SPEND ALL YOUR TIME READING
UP ON THIS AND STUFF, RIGHT?

89
00:05:07,456 --> 00:05:08,956
I JUST THOUGHT
THIS KIND OF KNIGHT,

90
00:05:08,956 --> 00:05:10,956
WELL, PROBABLY WOULDN'T BE...

91
00:05:10,956 --> 00:05:12,823
UM, FAKIR?

92
00:05:12,823 --> 00:05:15,089
-IF YOUR WOUNDS HAVE HEALED,
GO HOME.

93
00:05:15,089 --> 00:05:16,423
I'LL WALK YOU.

94
00:05:18,723 --> 00:05:20,956
-UM, ARE YOU MAD?

95
00:05:20,956 --> 00:05:23,723
-NO, NOT PARTICULARLY.

96
00:05:23,723 --> 00:05:25,589
-YOU ARE MAD.

97
00:05:29,056 --> 00:05:32,489
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR THE BANDAGE.

98
00:05:32,489 --> 00:05:33,389
-LATER.

99
00:05:33,389 --> 00:05:34,689
-GOOD NIGHT.

100
00:05:34,689 --> 00:05:38,056
-A PRINCE WHO CAN'T EVEN PROTECT
A PRINCESS.

101
00:05:38,056 --> 00:05:41,389
-YOU'RE A KNIGHT WHO COULDN'T
EVEN FIND THE STRENGTH TO DIE.

102
00:05:41,389 --> 00:05:42,423
WHAT CAN YOU DO?

103
00:05:42,423 --> 00:05:45,589
THE STORY
NO LONGER HAS NEED OF YOU.

104
00:05:45,589 --> 00:05:48,489
-DOES THAT MEAN THE STORY
WILL STAY EXACTLY THE SAME

105
00:05:48,489 --> 00:05:50,823
REGARDLESS
OF WHETHER I'M HERE OR NOT?

106
00:05:52,856 --> 00:05:55,123
-FAKIR WAS ACTING WEIRD,

107
00:05:55,123 --> 00:05:58,356
GETTING MAD
AND THEN SUDDENLY DEPRESSED.

108
00:05:58,356 --> 00:06:01,123
-OH, MS. DUCK!
WHY HAVEN'T YOU --

109
00:06:01,123 --> 00:06:02,123
-WATCH OUT!
-WATCH OUT!

110
00:06:02,123 --> 00:06:03,823
-YOU WERE JUST MERE CENTIMETERS

111
00:06:03,823 --> 00:06:05,123
FROM MARRYING MR. CAT!

112
00:06:05,123 --> 00:06:06,423
-OH, WELL, THANKS.

113
00:06:06,423 --> 00:06:09,423
-YOU WERE ALL SPACE OUT THINKING
ABOUT FAKIR, WEREN'T YOU?

114
00:06:09,423 --> 00:06:10,789
-NO! I --
[ GRUNTS ]

115
00:06:10,789 --> 00:06:12,489
-WANT TO TELL HIM HOW YOU FEEL?

116
00:06:12,489 --> 00:06:14,023
-IT'S NOT --
[ GROANS ]

117
00:06:14,023 --> 00:06:16,356
-SENDING A LOVE LETTER'S
A GREAT OPTION.

118
00:06:16,356 --> 00:06:18,256
-WHAT? NO, THAT'S --
[ GROANS ]

119
00:06:18,256 --> 00:06:19,689
-YOU'LL DO IT, WON'T YOU?

120
00:06:19,689 --> 00:06:22,089
I HAD A FEELING
THAT THIS MIGHT HAPPEN,

121
00:06:22,089 --> 00:06:24,089
SO I LOVE LETTER TO FAKIR
PREPARED.

122
00:06:24,089 --> 00:06:27,156
-IF YOU WANDER AROUND SCHOOL
CARRYING SOMETHING LIKE THAT,

123
00:06:27,156 --> 00:06:28,656
MS. BOTTOM IS BOUND TO COME,

124
00:06:28,656 --> 00:06:30,089
SO ASK HER
TO PASS IT ON FOR YOU.

125
00:06:30,089 --> 00:06:31,356
-MS. BOTTOM?

126
00:06:31,356 --> 00:06:33,756
-SHE GOES AND DELIVERS
LOVE LETTERS FOR PEOPLE.

127
00:06:33,756 --> 00:06:36,289
WORD IS, SHE KNOWS THE FEELINGS
OF PEOPLE IN LOVE.

128
00:06:36,289 --> 00:06:38,289
-SHE KNOWS THEIR FEELINGS?

129
00:06:38,289 --> 00:06:39,556
-Both: WE'LL CALL IT

130
00:06:39,556 --> 00:06:42,056
THE "GREAT LOVEY-DOVEY
LETTER OPERATION"!

131
00:06:42,056 --> 00:06:44,056
-UH, WELL,
BEST OF LUCK TO YOU.

132
00:06:44,056 --> 00:06:46,956
-COME ON! WE HAVE TO PREPARE
TO COMFORT HER LATER.

133
00:06:46,956 --> 00:06:47,789
-[ SIGHS ]

134
00:06:47,789 --> 00:06:49,189
A LOVE LETTER TO FAKIR.

135
00:06:49,189 --> 00:06:50,856
IF I GAVE HIM THIS, HE'D SAY,

136
00:06:50,856 --> 00:06:53,123
"DON'T WASTE TIME
ON TRIFLES, IDIOT,"

137
00:06:53,123 --> 00:06:54,923
OR SOMETHING KIND OF LIKE THAT.

138
00:06:54,923 --> 00:06:58,223
-OH, IT'S THAT IT, ZURA?
LOVEY-DOVEY, ZURA?

139
00:06:58,223 --> 00:07:00,623
-ALTHOUGH,
IF SHE KNOWS FEELINGS,

140
00:07:00,623 --> 00:07:03,823
I WONDER IF IT WOULD BE POSSIBLE
FOR ME TO TELL

141
00:07:03,823 --> 00:07:07,323
HOW MYTHO TRULY FEELS
IF COULD HAVE THAT SAME POWER.

142
00:07:07,323 --> 00:07:08,223
MS. BOTTOM.

143
00:07:08,223 --> 00:07:10,723
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

144
00:07:10,723 --> 00:07:11,889
-MY PRINCE?

145
00:07:11,889 --> 00:07:14,389
AREN'T YOU HERE, MY PRINCE?

146
00:07:14,389 --> 00:07:15,423
WHAT IS THIS?

147
00:07:15,423 --> 00:07:17,989
IT LOOKS AS IF HE FOUGHT
WITH SOMEONE.

148
00:07:17,989 --> 00:07:18,856
[ GASPS ]

149
00:07:20,889 --> 00:07:22,323
COULD IT BE?

150
00:07:22,323 --> 00:07:27,589
IS THIS NEWEST HEART SHARD
AFFECTING HIM SO VIOLENTLY?

151
00:07:27,589 --> 00:07:29,056
-[ PANTING ]

152
00:07:34,223 --> 00:07:37,823
I MUST OVERCOME
THIS RAVEN'S BLOOD IN ME

153
00:07:37,823 --> 00:07:41,823
AND UPHOLD MY PRIDE AS A PRINCE.

154
00:07:41,823 --> 00:07:45,856
-I WONDER WHAT KIND OF PERSON
MS. BOTTOM IS.

155
00:07:47,356 --> 00:07:48,523
-HUH?

156
00:07:48,523 --> 00:07:50,123
[ GASPS ]

157
00:07:50,123 --> 00:07:52,889
-ARE YOU AGONIZING
OVER YOUR LOVE?

158
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:55,389
-ARE YOU MS. BOTTOM?

159
00:07:55,389 --> 00:07:56,689
D-DONKEY?!

160
00:07:56,689 --> 00:07:59,556
-I'M BOTTOM, FRIEND OF ALL THOSE
WHO ARE IN LOVE.

161
00:07:59,556 --> 00:08:01,556
SO, WHERE'S YOUR LETTER?
-UH...

162
00:08:01,556 --> 00:08:04,656
-YOUR TAIL IS NOT A TAIL, ZURA.

163
00:08:04,656 --> 00:08:07,089
WHERE'S YOUR TAIL, ZURA?
-[ GASPS ]

164
00:08:07,089 --> 00:08:09,123
[ SCREAMS ]
-UH, MS. BOTTOM?

165
00:08:09,123 --> 00:08:10,289
-AH.

166
00:08:10,289 --> 00:08:12,289
♪ DONKEY-LONKEY,
LOVEY-DOVEY, DONKEY! ♪

167
00:08:12,289 --> 00:08:15,056
-MS. BOTTOM?
MS. BOTTOM!

168
00:08:15,056 --> 00:08:17,089
OH!

169
00:08:17,089 --> 00:08:18,823
-[ PANTING ]

170
00:08:18,823 --> 00:08:20,556
-MS. BOTTOM?

171
00:08:20,556 --> 00:08:21,589
-HUH? AAH!

172
00:08:21,589 --> 00:08:23,056
NO! YOU'VE GOT IT ALL WRONG.

173
00:08:23,056 --> 00:08:25,189
I'M NOT BOTTOM
OR ANYBODY WHO HAS TO DO

174
00:08:25,189 --> 00:08:26,489
WITH LOVE LETTERS AND --

175
00:08:26,489 --> 00:08:29,189
-AREN'T YOU THAT UPPERCLASSMAN
I SEE AROUND?

176
00:08:29,189 --> 00:08:31,256
-[ SIGHS ]
YOU FOUND ME OUT.

177
00:08:31,256 --> 00:08:32,589
ANYWAY, I'M HERMIA.

178
00:08:32,589 --> 00:08:34,623
PLEASE DON'T TELL ANYONE, OKAY?

179
00:08:34,623 --> 00:08:37,456
I'LL MAKE SURE
YOUR LETTER GETS DELIVERED.

180
00:08:37,456 --> 00:08:38,623
-OH, NO, THAT'S OKAY.

181
00:08:38,623 --> 00:08:40,956
MY FRIEND WAS THE ONE
WHO WROTE IT FOR ME,

182
00:08:40,956 --> 00:08:42,989
BUT SHE'S KIND OF GOT
THE WRONG IDEA

183
00:08:42,989 --> 00:08:44,656
ABOUT WHICH PERSON I LIKE, SO...

184
00:08:44,656 --> 00:08:45,656
-OH.

185
00:08:45,656 --> 00:08:47,056
-BY THE WAY, I'M DUCK.

186
00:08:47,056 --> 00:08:48,123
-MS. DUCK, HUH?

187
00:08:48,123 --> 00:08:50,789
WELL, WHEN YOU'VE WRITTEN
YOUR REAL LETTER,

188
00:08:50,789 --> 00:08:53,089
BRING IT TO ME ANY TIME, OKAY?
-OH.

189
00:08:53,089 --> 00:08:57,389
I WOULD, BUT CIRCUMSTANCES
KEEP ME FROM CONFESSING MY LOVE.

190
00:08:57,389 --> 00:08:59,156
-I SEE.

191
00:08:59,156 --> 00:09:02,423
-UM, MS. HERMIA,
DO YOU KNOW PEOPLE'S FEELINGS?

192
00:09:02,423 --> 00:09:04,256
-WHAT?
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

193
00:09:04,256 --> 00:09:07,389
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT SOMETIMES I CAN SENSE THEM,

194
00:09:07,389 --> 00:09:09,956
LIKE,
"AH, THIS PERSON IS IN LOVE,"

195
00:09:09,956 --> 00:09:11,523
OR, "SHE LOOKS LONELY.

196
00:09:11,523 --> 00:09:14,556
MAYBE SHE'S SUFFERING
FROM A BROKEN HEART."

197
00:09:14,556 --> 00:09:16,989
-WOW!
-I'M FAIRLY TALL, YOU KNOW,

198
00:09:16,989 --> 00:09:20,289
SO I'M ALWAYS THE ONE FURTHEST
TO THE BACK OF THE CORPS.

199
00:09:20,289 --> 00:09:22,456
BUT ONE DAY,
I NOTICED I COULD SEE

200
00:09:22,456 --> 00:09:26,456
THE FEELING OF BEING IN LOVE
WRITTEN ON EVERYONE'S BACKS --

201
00:09:26,456 --> 00:09:29,589
THE HEART-RENDING FEELING
OF PEOPLE IN LOVE.

202
00:09:29,589 --> 00:09:31,423
LOVE IS A WONDERFUL THING,

203
00:09:31,423 --> 00:09:35,089
BUT IT ALSO MAKES PEOPLE SUFFER
AND BE SAD, RIGHT?

204
00:09:35,089 --> 00:09:38,756
SO, EVERYONE HAS A HARD TIME
SAYING, "I LOVE YOU,"

205
00:09:38,756 --> 00:09:42,156
AND THEY'RE ALL KEEPING
THEIR FEELINGS INSIDE.

206
00:09:42,156 --> 00:09:44,456
I THOUGHT
I'D AT LEAST LIKE TO TRY AND SEE

207
00:09:44,456 --> 00:09:47,323
IF THERE WAS SOMETHING
I COULD DO TO HELP THOSE PEOPLE.

208
00:09:47,323 --> 00:09:48,156
-I SEE.

209
00:09:48,156 --> 00:09:49,323
-BUT, YOU KNOW,

210
00:09:49,323 --> 00:09:52,389
LATELY IT'S ALL BEEN LETTERS
WRITTEN TO MYTHO.

211
00:09:52,389 --> 00:09:54,889
-WRITTEN TO MYTHO?
-YES.

212
00:09:54,889 --> 00:09:57,123
I BRING HIM LOTS OF LETTERS
EVERY DAY.

213
00:09:57,123 --> 00:09:59,223
MOST ARE FROM PEOPLE
WHOSE FEELINGS

214
00:09:59,223 --> 00:10:01,389
ULTIMATELY
WON'T BE RETURNED, THOUGH.

215
00:10:01,389 --> 00:10:04,423
-I GUESS YOU MUST SEE MYTHO
PRETTY MUCH EVERY DAY, THEN,

216
00:10:04,423 --> 00:10:05,389
HUH, MS. HERMIA?

217
00:10:05,389 --> 00:10:06,856
-YES.

218
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,556
WELL, ACTUALLY, THE ODD THING
IS, MYTHO USUALLY COMES TO ME.

219
00:10:09,556 --> 00:10:11,989
-SO, THEN, YOU KNOW SOMETHING
ABOUT MYTHO'S FEELINGS,

220
00:10:11,989 --> 00:10:12,956
DON'T YOU?
-HUH?

221
00:10:12,956 --> 00:10:14,323
-ANYTHING IS FINE!

222
00:10:14,323 --> 00:10:15,756
-I'M SORRY.

223
00:10:15,756 --> 00:10:19,389
MYTHO'S FEELINGS ARE THE ONE
PERSON'S I CAN'T SEEM TO READ.

224
00:10:19,389 --> 00:10:20,856
-OH, I SEE.

225
00:10:20,856 --> 00:10:24,189
-OH, ARE YOU BY ANY CHANCE ONE
OF THOSE WHO LIKES MYTHO, TOO?

226
00:10:24,189 --> 00:10:25,389
-HUH? OH!

227
00:10:25,389 --> 00:10:27,889
I GUESS YOU MUST LIKE HIM, TOO,
HUH, MS. HERMIA?

228
00:10:27,889 --> 00:10:30,056
-NO, NO, NO!
YOU'VE GOT IT ALL WRONG!

229
00:10:30,056 --> 00:10:32,156
I DON'T HAVE ANY FEELINGS
FOR MYTHO!

230
00:10:32,156 --> 00:10:34,889
I HAVE SOMEONE ELSE I LIKE!
HIS NAME IS LYSANDER!

231
00:10:34,889 --> 00:10:38,223
-MR. LYSANDER?

232
00:10:38,223 --> 00:10:39,856
-UH-HUH.

233
00:10:46,889 --> 00:10:51,356
-I HAVE TO GET
MORE HEART SHARDS BACK.

234
00:10:54,389 --> 00:10:56,356
K-KRAEHE.

235
00:11:08,956 --> 00:11:12,956
-WHO DOES THE PRINCE'S HEART
BELONG TO?

236
00:11:12,956 --> 00:11:15,723
AND WHERE IS THE REST OF IT?

237
00:11:15,723 --> 00:11:17,556
THAT IS A SECRET.

238
00:11:17,556 --> 00:11:19,389
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

239
00:11:19,389 --> 00:11:22,856
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "MARCH"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

240
00:11:35,489 --> 00:11:37,956
-[ PANTING ]

241
00:11:48,948 --> 00:11:51,248
-MY PRINCE.

242
00:11:51,248 --> 00:11:54,781
YOU NEEDN'T SUFFER ANYMORE.

243
00:11:54,781 --> 00:11:57,448
YOUR PRINCESS IS I.

244
00:11:57,448 --> 00:12:02,881
I WILL RESCUE YOU
FROM YOUR SUFFERING AND PAIN.

245
00:12:05,181 --> 00:12:10,281
RETURN, PRINCE OF THE CROWS.
RETURN TO ME.

246
00:12:12,581 --> 00:12:16,581
-I WILL NOT BECOME
THE PRINCE OF THE CROWS.

247
00:12:16,581 --> 00:12:21,148
-IF YOU RESIST, YOUR SUFFERING
WILL JUST CONTINUE.

248
00:12:21,148 --> 00:12:23,381
-I CAN HANDLE SUFFERING.

249
00:12:23,381 --> 00:12:26,048
-YOU HAVE RAVEN'S BLOOD
RUNNING THROUGH YOUR VEINS

250
00:12:26,048 --> 00:12:28,281
JUST LIKE I DO.

251
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:29,848
NO ONE CAN ERASE IT.

252
00:12:29,848 --> 00:12:31,814
NO ONE CAN STOP IT.

253
00:12:34,381 --> 00:12:40,081
I WILL LOVE YOU MORE DEEPLY
THAN ANYONE ELSE CAN.

254
00:12:40,081 --> 00:12:42,881
I'LL GIVE YOU MY LOVE.

255
00:12:45,081 --> 00:12:49,381
-YOU'LL GIVE ME YOUR LOVE?
HOW KIND.

256
00:12:49,381 --> 00:12:50,214
-[ GASPS ]

257
00:12:50,214 --> 00:12:51,714
-IT'S GOOD TO KNOW

258
00:12:51,714 --> 00:12:55,181
YOUR LOVE SEEKS
ITS NATURAL OBJECT, PRINCESS.

259
00:12:55,181 --> 00:12:58,748
YOU OUGHT TO LOVE ME MORE.
ME ALONE.

260
00:12:58,748 --> 00:13:00,114
[ SHUDDERS ]

261
00:13:00,114 --> 00:13:02,014
[ BIRDS SQUAWKING ]

262
00:13:02,014 --> 00:13:03,348
[ GRUNTS ]

263
00:13:03,348 --> 00:13:04,514
-PRINCE?

264
00:13:04,514 --> 00:13:07,914
-NOT ENOUGH.
NOT ENOUGH LOVE.

265
00:13:07,914 --> 00:13:10,648
[ BIRDS SCREECHING ]

266
00:13:10,648 --> 00:13:12,181
-SHUT UP!

267
00:13:12,181 --> 00:13:13,614
-[ GASPS ]

268
00:13:13,614 --> 00:13:16,081
SEE, LYSANDER
IS SOMEONE IN MY GRADE

269
00:13:16,081 --> 00:13:17,914
FROM THE SCULPTURE DIVISION.

270
00:13:17,914 --> 00:13:20,114
THIS IS ONE OF HIS WORKS.
-WOW!

271
00:13:20,114 --> 00:13:23,348
-YOUR HEART GETS WARM
JUST LOOKING AT IT, DOESN'T IT?

272
00:13:23,348 --> 00:13:24,414
-HUH? YEAH.

273
00:13:24,414 --> 00:13:26,881
-IT'S AS IF THE SCULPTURE
IS SOMEHOW FILLED

274
00:13:26,881 --> 00:13:28,948
WITH THE WARM AND TENDER
FEELING OF LOVE.

275
00:13:28,948 --> 00:13:30,114
-RIGHT.

276
00:13:30,114 --> 00:13:32,481
-HE MUST HAVE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT SOMEONE

277
00:13:32,481 --> 00:13:33,681
WHILE HE CREATED IT.

278
00:13:33,681 --> 00:13:35,681
-IT MIGHT HAVE BEEN YOU,
MISS HERMIA.

279
00:13:35,681 --> 00:13:36,814
-NO, DEFINITELY NOT!

280
00:13:36,814 --> 00:13:38,914
I KNOW MYSELF
BETTER THAN ANYONE ELSE.

281
00:13:38,914 --> 00:13:40,148
THAT'S SO --
-HUH?

282
00:13:41,914 --> 00:13:44,848
IS THAT MR. LYSANDER?

283
00:13:44,848 --> 00:13:46,081
-YEAH.

284
00:13:46,081 --> 00:13:48,148
DOESN'T HE EXUDE KINDNESS?

285
00:13:48,148 --> 00:13:52,648
-UH...S-SURE.

286
00:13:52,648 --> 00:13:55,381
-AAH!
-AAH!

287
00:13:55,381 --> 00:13:56,414
-[ MEOWS ]

288
00:13:56,414 --> 00:13:58,714
-IT'S THE MIME FOR,
"DO YOU MEAN ME?"

289
00:13:58,714 --> 00:13:59,648
-[ SQUEALING ]

290
00:13:59,648 --> 00:14:01,214
-WHAT'S THAT MIME
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

291
00:14:01,214 --> 00:14:04,048
THE -- THE MIME FOR MARRIAGE!

292
00:14:04,048 --> 00:14:06,081
-[ SCREAMING ]
-I DON'T KNOW THAT ONE.

293
00:14:06,081 --> 00:14:08,248
THE MIME FOR VOW!

294
00:14:08,248 --> 00:14:09,114
-UH --

295
00:14:09,114 --> 00:14:10,481
-UH! OH!
THE MIME FOR NO.

296
00:14:10,481 --> 00:14:14,214
-[ YOWLING ]

297
00:14:14,214 --> 00:14:16,814
-THAT WAS A CLOSE CALL.
-[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

298
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:17,848
HUH?

299
00:14:17,848 --> 00:14:21,448
-WHY DON'T YOU WRITE
A LOVE LETTER?

300
00:14:21,448 --> 00:14:22,381
-[ HUMMING ]

301
00:14:22,381 --> 00:14:24,314
-QUACK!
-WHAT'S THAT SOUND?

302
00:14:24,314 --> 00:14:26,914
-OH, UH,
SOMETHING IMPORTANT'S COME UP.

303
00:14:26,914 --> 00:14:28,414
THAT IS, WELL -- GOODBYE!

304
00:14:28,414 --> 00:14:29,314
-HUH?

305
00:14:29,314 --> 00:14:30,781
[ SIGHS ]

306
00:14:33,481 --> 00:14:35,614
-[ HUMMING ]

307
00:14:35,614 --> 00:14:37,981
-OH, NOT GOOD!

308
00:14:37,981 --> 00:14:39,348
-[ HUMMING ]

309
00:14:39,348 --> 00:14:41,214
-UH, FAKIR!

310
00:14:41,214 --> 00:14:42,348
[ GRUNTS ]

311
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:44,581
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING
PLAYING WITH UZURA?

312
00:14:44,581 --> 00:14:47,214
-WOULD YOU MIND BEING
A LITTLE QUIETER UP THERE?

313
00:14:47,214 --> 00:14:48,948
-SORRY.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

314
00:14:48,948 --> 00:14:51,981
OH, FAKIR,
RESEARCHING IN BOOKS AGAIN, HUH?

315
00:14:51,981 --> 00:14:54,914
-I'M JUST DOING WHAT I CAN,
HOWEVER SMALL.

316
00:14:54,914 --> 00:14:56,848
I HAVEN'T CAST OFF MY SWORD.

317
00:14:56,848 --> 00:14:58,081
-OH, RIGHT.

318
00:14:58,081 --> 00:15:00,948
COME ON, UZURA.
WE'RE IN THE WAY, SO LET'S GO.

319
00:15:00,948 --> 00:15:02,348
-[ HUMMING LOUDLY ]

320
00:15:02,348 --> 00:15:04,414
-HOW MANY TIMES
MUST I TELL YOU?!

321
00:15:04,414 --> 00:15:05,948
-SORRY!

322
00:15:05,948 --> 00:15:09,981
-WHY?
WHY AM I SO OBSESSED WITH BOOKS?

323
00:15:09,981 --> 00:15:12,281
NO MATTER
WHAT BOOK I OPEN, THOUGH,

324
00:15:12,281 --> 00:15:14,681
THEY'VE ALL HAD THE ENDINGS
TORN OUT.

325
00:15:14,681 --> 00:15:17,081
THE GHOST KNIGHT'S BOOK
WAS THE SAME.

326
00:15:17,081 --> 00:15:19,848
BUT I SAW THE END OF THAT BOOK
IN MY DREAMS.

327
00:15:19,848 --> 00:15:21,848
DAMN IT!
WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

328
00:15:21,848 --> 00:15:24,181
-WE HAVE TO BE QUIET
IN THE LIBRARY.

329
00:15:24,181 --> 00:15:26,848
-THAT UNDERDEVELOPED HERMIA,
OF ALL PEOPLE!

330
00:15:26,848 --> 00:15:29,081
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
SHE'S WITH MYTHO!

331
00:15:29,081 --> 00:15:31,048
-OH, THIS IS SO VEXING!
-OH, THIS IS SO VEXING!

332
00:15:31,048 --> 00:15:32,948
-HUH?

333
00:15:32,948 --> 00:15:34,614
UM, EXCUSE ME.
-Both: HUH?

334
00:15:34,614 --> 00:15:37,348
-DID SOMETHING HAPPEN
WITH MYTHO AND MISS HERMIA?

335
00:15:37,348 --> 00:15:39,814
-"SOMETHING," SHE SAYS!
-THEY'RE ON A DATE.

336
00:15:39,814 --> 00:15:43,148
-HOLDING HANDS AND GOING TOWARDS
THE GROVE BEHIND THE SCHOOL!

337
00:15:43,148 --> 00:15:45,414
-BEHIND THE SCHOOL?
-WHAT A SHOCK, HUH?

338
00:15:45,414 --> 00:15:46,581
-WANT TO DIG, TOO?

339
00:15:46,581 --> 00:15:49,114
-OH, NO. THAT'S OKAY.
UH, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

340
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:52,981
-HERMIA -- OR PERHAPS
SHOULD I SAY BOTTOM THE DONKEY?

341
00:15:52,981 --> 00:15:56,548
-DID YOU KNOW I WAS
BOTTOM THE DONKEY ALL ALONG?

342
00:15:56,548 --> 00:16:00,614
-YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE I'VE BEEN
LOOKING AT ALL THIS TIME.

343
00:16:00,614 --> 00:16:04,481
I KNOW EVERYTHING -- THE FACT
THAT YOU LIKE LYSANDER INCLUDED.

344
00:16:04,481 --> 00:16:07,381
-UM, HERE.
THESE ARE TODAY'S LETTERS.

345
00:16:07,381 --> 00:16:09,181
-THAT RUBBISH?
-HUH?

346
00:16:09,181 --> 00:16:11,581
-YOU ARE MY PRINCESS.
-UH?

347
00:16:11,581 --> 00:16:14,781
-YOU ARE MINE AND MINE ALONE,
HERMIA.

348
00:16:18,738 --> 00:16:21,672
YOU DON'T HAVE THE COURAGE
TO CONFESS YOUR OWN LOVE.

349
00:16:21,672 --> 00:16:25,105
YOU'RE DELIVERING OTHER PEOPLE'S
LETTERS JUST TO FOOL YOURSELF.

350
00:16:25,105 --> 00:16:27,205
-YOU'RE WRONG.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I --

351
00:16:27,205 --> 00:16:29,205
-YOU MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
GOOD WILL,

352
00:16:29,205 --> 00:16:30,705
BUT IT'S ALL FOR YOURSELF.

353
00:16:30,705 --> 00:16:32,172
LET'S BE HONEST.
-I --

354
00:16:32,172 --> 00:16:34,238
-BUT, YOU KNOW, THAT'S FINE.
-HUH?

355
00:16:34,238 --> 00:16:37,738
-BECAUSE EVERYBODY ELSE
IS JUST USING YOU, TOO.

356
00:16:37,738 --> 00:16:39,472
YOU MIGHT AS WELL FOCUS

357
00:16:39,472 --> 00:16:42,272
EXCLUSIVELY ON YOURSELF
FROM NOW ON.

358
00:16:42,272 --> 00:16:46,305
IF YOU LOVE ME, YOU WON'T
HAVE TO FOOL YOURSELF ANYMORE.

359
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:49,105
LOVE ONLY ME
AND HATE EVERYONE ELSE.

360
00:16:49,105 --> 00:16:51,805
-YES, I WILL LOVE
ONLY YOU, MYTHO,

361
00:16:51,805 --> 00:16:54,972
AND I WILL HATE EVERYONE ELSE
FROM NOW ON.

362
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:56,972
-THEN AS PROOF,

363
00:16:56,972 --> 00:17:02,138
YOU'LL GIVE ME
YOUR BEAUTIFUL HEART, WON'T YOU?

364
00:17:02,138 --> 00:17:03,338
-I WILL.

365
00:17:03,338 --> 00:17:04,805
-THEN COME.

366
00:17:04,805 --> 00:17:09,572
DANCE INTO MY ARMS
AND GIVE ME YOUR HEART.

367
00:17:12,038 --> 00:17:16,372
-IF I HAVE YOU, I CAN BECOME
A PRIMA BALLERINA, CAN'T I?

368
00:17:16,372 --> 00:17:20,272
I'M SICK OF BEING THE GO-BETWEEN
FOR OTHER PEOPLE.

369
00:17:20,272 --> 00:17:23,872
I WILL ACT FOR MY OWN SAKE,
FOR MYTHO'S SAKE.

370
00:17:23,872 --> 00:17:25,005
-YES.

371
00:17:25,005 --> 00:17:27,872
COME AND SACRIFICE YOUR LIFE
FOR MY SAKE.

372
00:17:27,872 --> 00:17:30,338
-[ GASPS ]
MISS HERMIA!

373
00:17:48,505 --> 00:17:52,872
MISS HERMIA,
DON'T GO OVER THERE.

374
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:56,305
-ARE YOU GOING TO INTERFERE?

375
00:17:56,305 --> 00:18:01,072
-PLEASE COME AND DANCE WITH ME,
MISS HERMIA.

376
00:18:01,072 --> 00:18:02,605
-DANCE WITH YOU?

377
00:18:02,605 --> 00:18:05,105
-HERMIA, HURRY AND COME HERE.

378
00:18:05,105 --> 00:18:08,372
GIVE ME YOUR LOVE NOW.
I DEMAND IT.

379
00:18:08,372 --> 00:18:10,305
-YES.
I'M COMING.

380
00:18:14,638 --> 00:18:16,872
-GOOD, MY LOYAL MAID.

381
00:18:16,872 --> 00:18:19,372
HERE, COME INTO MY ARMS.

382
00:18:19,372 --> 00:18:22,838
-MISS HERMIA,
IS THAT REALLY ALL RIGHT?

383
00:18:22,838 --> 00:18:25,538
IS IT ALL RIGHT TO END YOUR LOVE

384
00:18:25,538 --> 00:18:28,638
WITHOUT EVER
HAVING SAID ANYTHING?

385
00:18:28,638 --> 00:18:30,005
-IT'S FINE!

386
00:18:30,005 --> 00:18:32,872
YOU CAN JUST THROW AWAY
A MEANINGLESS LOVE LIKE THAT.

387
00:18:32,872 --> 00:18:35,938
-YES. SUCH A LOVE
SHOULD BE CAST ASIDE.

388
00:18:35,938 --> 00:18:39,005
-THAT'S NOT TRUE.
IT ISN'T MEANINGLESS.

389
00:18:39,005 --> 00:18:42,538
IT'S A PRECIOUS FEELING
OF YOURS, MISS HERMIA.

390
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:45,972
IT IS STILL LOVE
WHETHER YOU SPEAK IT OR NOT.

391
00:18:45,972 --> 00:18:49,105
AND IF THAT TRULY
IS A PRECIOUS FEELING,

392
00:18:49,105 --> 00:18:51,838
IT WOULD ONLY BE CRUELTY
TO THROW IT AWAY.

393
00:18:51,838 --> 00:18:55,405
I DON'T WANT YOU TO HIDE
THAT FEELING ON YOUR BACK.

394
00:18:55,405 --> 00:18:57,638
I WANT YOU TO TELL HIM ABOUT IT.

395
00:19:00,338 --> 00:19:03,872
IF I WERE ALLOWED,
I WOULD, ALSO.

396
00:19:03,872 --> 00:19:06,238
IF I WERE ONLY ALLOWED.

397
00:19:06,238 --> 00:19:08,672
-[ GRUNTING ]

398
00:19:11,238 --> 00:19:14,838
BE GONE FROM INSIDE ME, RAVEN!

399
00:19:14,838 --> 00:19:16,738
-YES.
THAT'S RIGHT.

400
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:19,805
I HAVEN'T --
I HAVEN'T TOLD LYSANDER

401
00:19:19,805 --> 00:19:23,338
ANYTHING ABOUT THIS YET,
ABOUT MY FEELINGS.

402
00:19:23,338 --> 00:19:24,438
-YES.

403
00:19:26,305 --> 00:19:28,238
THE FEELING THAT HAS GROWN

404
00:19:28,238 --> 00:19:30,872
TO THE BURSTING POINT
INSIDE YOU,

405
00:19:30,872 --> 00:19:32,305
THAT IS REAL LOVE.

406
00:19:32,305 --> 00:19:33,705
-THAT'S RIGHT.

407
00:19:33,705 --> 00:19:36,872
WHAT YOU'RE SEEKING
IS FALSE LOVE.

408
00:19:36,872 --> 00:19:38,838
IT'S COUNTERFEIT LOVE.

409
00:19:38,838 --> 00:19:39,805
SHUT UP!

410
00:19:39,805 --> 00:19:42,305
WHAT IS THIS "REAL LOVE"?

411
00:19:42,305 --> 00:19:44,872
IF THE LOVE I'M SEEKING
IS FALSE LOVE,

412
00:19:44,872 --> 00:19:47,805
THEN ALL THE LOVE IN THE WORLD
MUST BE FALSE!

413
00:19:47,805 --> 00:19:50,772
[ WIND RUSTLING ]

414
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:53,538
-[ SIGHS ]
-MISS HERMIA.

415
00:19:53,538 --> 00:19:57,038
-LYSANDER!

416
00:19:57,038 --> 00:19:59,538
-MM.

417
00:19:59,538 --> 00:20:01,705
-[ GASPS ]

418
00:20:01,705 --> 00:20:02,838
OH?

419
00:20:02,838 --> 00:20:04,838
AHH!

420
00:20:04,838 --> 00:20:10,072
[ LAUGHS ] I JUST FOUND
DUCK'S LOVEY-DOVEY, ZURA!

421
00:20:16,738 --> 00:20:17,805
-YES?

422
00:20:21,438 --> 00:20:22,838
-UH.

423
00:20:22,838 --> 00:20:25,805
-UM, UH, WELL, LYSANDER, I --

424
00:20:25,805 --> 00:20:27,138
YOU MUST BE SURPRISED

425
00:20:27,138 --> 00:20:29,338
AT ME SAYING THIS
OUT OF THE BLUE,

426
00:20:29,338 --> 00:20:32,872
BUT, YOU SEE, WELL, I...

427
00:20:32,872 --> 00:20:36,905
LYSANDER, I WANTED TO SAY...

428
00:20:36,905 --> 00:20:38,838
I LOVE YOU.

429
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:42,338
-UH...UH...

430
00:20:42,338 --> 00:20:43,705
-HMM?

431
00:20:43,705 --> 00:20:44,538
-[ GASPS ]

432
00:20:44,538 --> 00:20:47,338
-COULD THAT BE...?

433
00:20:47,338 --> 00:20:49,105
-I MADE YOU MY MODEL
WITHOUT ASKING

434
00:20:49,105 --> 00:20:51,205
'CAUSE I THOUGHT I'D CONFESS
MY LOVE TO YOU

435
00:20:51,205 --> 00:20:52,872
ONCE I FINISHED IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

436
00:20:58,305 --> 00:20:59,172
-HEY.

437
00:20:59,172 --> 00:21:00,005
-WHAT?

438
00:21:00,005 --> 00:21:01,572
-UZURA BROUGHT THIS TO ME.

439
00:21:01,572 --> 00:21:02,705
-AAH!

440
00:21:02,705 --> 00:21:04,805
I-I DIDN'T WRITE IT.
PIKE AND LILIE WROTE IT.

441
00:21:04,805 --> 00:21:06,172
SO, WHAT SHOULD I SAY?

442
00:21:06,172 --> 00:21:08,405
UM, I'M SORRY?

443
00:21:08,405 --> 00:21:10,172
-[ SIGHS ]

444
00:21:10,172 --> 00:21:13,605
DON'T WASTE TIME ON TRIFLES,
IDIOT.

445
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:16,238
-I KNEW IT.

446
00:21:16,238 --> 00:21:18,938
-REAL LOVE, IS IT?
DON'T MAKE ME LAUGH.

447
00:21:18,938 --> 00:21:21,905
EVERYONE JUST WANTS TO BE LOVED.
THAT'S ALL.

448
00:21:21,905 --> 00:21:24,372
-MY POOR, DEAR PRINCE.
DON'T WORRY.

449
00:21:24,372 --> 00:21:27,172
I'M POSITIVE FATHER'S BLOOD
WILL SAVE YOU

450
00:21:27,172 --> 00:21:29,172
FROM YOUR SUFFERING QUITE SOON.

451
00:21:29,172 --> 00:21:32,205
-THAT'S RIGHT.
WE HAVE TO FIND A SACRIFICE.

452
00:21:32,205 --> 00:21:35,038
-OF COURSE.
FOR OUR OWN SAKES, TOO.

453
00:21:35,038 --> 00:21:36,072
[ GASPS ]

454
00:21:36,072 --> 00:21:37,938
-THIS ISN'T FOR YOU.

455
00:21:37,938 --> 00:21:42,038
I'M GOING TO FEED THE FOOLISH
RAVEN A MEAL, THAT'S ALL.

456
00:21:42,038 --> 00:21:46,338
AS A SMALL TOKEN OF MY GRATITUDE
FOR HELPING TO AWAKEN ME.

457
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:47,505
-THAT'S RIGHT.

458
00:21:47,505 --> 00:21:48,838
THIS IS THE STORY

459
00:21:48,838 --> 00:21:51,838
OF THE PRINCE AND THE RAVEN,
ISN'T IT?

460
00:21:51,838 --> 00:21:54,038
THE FIGHT BEGAN LONG, LONG AGO.

461
00:21:54,038 --> 00:21:57,038
BUT THEIR AGE-OLD ENMITY
IS STILL FRESH.

462
00:21:57,038 --> 00:22:01,438
YOU HAVEN'T FORGOTTEN THAT, NOW,
HAVE YOU, DEAR, LITTLE DUCK?

463
00:22:01,438 --> 00:22:04,772
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

464
00:22:04,772 --> 00:22:07,472
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S "THOUGH
MY LOVE IS SMALL" PLAYS ]

465
00:22:19,005 --> 00:22:21,805
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

466
00:23:34,705 --> 00:23:36,238
-WHO IS SHE, DE-FANGING

467
00:23:36,238 --> 00:23:38,538
THE BITINGLY SARCASTIC,
FANTASTIC FAKIR?

468
00:23:38,538 --> 00:23:41,105
-AN OLDER WOMAN LOVER, HUH?
-THE STORIES THAT BOY

469
00:23:41,105 --> 00:23:43,805
USED TO WRITE NOW AND AGAIN,
SOMETIMES THEY CAME TRUE.

470
00:23:43,805 --> 00:23:46,105
-I'LL PROTECT MYTHO AS A KNIGHT.
END OF STORY.

471
00:23:46,105 --> 00:23:47,338
I WON'T TAKE ORDERS FROM YOU!

472
00:23:47,338 --> 00:23:48,705
-AND IT WAS STARTING
TO LOOK LIKE

473
00:23:48,705 --> 00:23:50,105
WE'D BE ABLE
TO WORK TOGETHER, TOO.

474
00:23:50,105 --> 00:23:51,305
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

475
00:23:51,305 --> 00:23:53,738
-MYTHO, I WILL NOT ALLOW YOU
TO HARM RACHEL.

476
00:23:53,738 --> 00:23:56,438
-STOP! THE TWO OF YOU FIGHTING,
IT'S NOT GOING TO --

477
00:23:56,438 --> 00:23:58,605
-YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T LAY
A FINGER ON ME, FAKIR.

478
00:23:58,605 --> 00:24:03,072
-OH, YOU CHILDREN WHO LOVE
STORIES, COME, GATHER 'ROUND.

479
00:24:03,072 --> 00:24:04,572
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

